
DESCRIPTION OF THE ORGANIZATION (SIZE, TYPE, PRODUCT OR SERVICE, ETC.):


The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. is an American multinational finance company that engages in global investment banking, investment management, securities, and other financial services including asset management, mergers and acquisitions advice, prime brokerage, and securities underwriting services. It also sponsors private equity funds, is a market maker, and is a primary dealer in the United States Treasury security market. Goldman Sachs also owns GS Bank USA, a direct bank.



POSITION DESCRIPTION (DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES, ETC.):

Position: Summer Technology Analyst

Description: I worked with the Mobile Team at the technology division of Goldman Sachs. I was responsible for investigating various speech recognition and natural language processing libraries and implementing them to build a prototype of voice assistant that can be further used at the organization, keeping in mind the various data security constraints of the company.  

